Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe Arewa Youth Consultative Forum, AYCF, has said Nigerian youths will shock presidential aspirants like Bola Tinubu and Atiku Abubakar in the 2023 presidential election.
AYCF National President, Yerima Shettima said Nigerian youths will put Atiku and Tinubu where they belong in 2023.
According to him, the youths are determined to go all out in ensuring that the All Progressives Congress, APC, National Leader, and former Vice President never become the country’s President.
“Nobody will give them that chance this time around, but certainly, the youths of this country would make a statement at a given time, you can be rest assured of this,” he told he Daily Post.
“Nobody will stop them from contesting, but certainly nobody will give them a chance; we will drag it together. We will ensure that we use our large number, consult widely, and ensure we put them where they belong.”
Tinubu and Atiku are the two top-shots among the lots aspiring to rule Nigeria in 2023.
Others who have declared intention include PDP drop-in Dele Momodu, APC Gov Dave Umahi, Sen. Rochas Okorocha, Sahara Reporters publisher Omoyele Sowore, and others.
